verses.text:
And the priest of his sons that is anointed in his stead shall
offer it: \add it is\add* a statute for ever unto the \nd LORD\nd*;
it shall be wholly burnt.

This \add is\add* the law of the burnt offering, of the meat
offering, and of the sin offering, and of the trespass offering,
and of the consecrations, and of the sacrifice of the peace offerings;

Take Aaron and his sons with him, and the garments, and the
anointing oil, and a bullock for the sin offering, and two rams,
and a basket of unleavened bread;

And he put the mitre upon his head; also upon the mitre, \add even\add*
upon his forefront, did he put the golden plate, the holy crown;
as the \nd LORD\nd* commanded Moses.

And unto the children of Israel thou shalt speak, saying, Take
ye a kid of the goats for a sin offering; and a calf and a lamb,
\add both\add* of the first year, without blemish, for a burnt offering;

Yet these may ye eat of every flying creeping thing that goeth upon
\add all\add* four, which have legs above their feet, to leap withal
upon the earth;

And if a leprosy break out abroad in the skin, and the leprosy
cover all the skin of \add him that hath\add* the plague from his
head even to his foot, wheresoever the priest looketh;

And in the seventh day the priest shall look on the plague: and, behold,
\add if\add* the scall spread not, and there be in it no yellow hair,
and the scall \add be\add* not in sight deeper than the skin;

And if the priest shall look, and, behold, the plague be not
spread in the garment, either in the warp, or in the woof, or in any
thing of skin;

And the priest shall go forth out of the camp; and the priest
shall look, and, behold, \add if\add* the plague of leprosy be healed
in the leper;

When ye be come into the land of Canaan, which I give to you for a
possession, and I put the plague of leprosy in a house of the land
of your possession;

And the priest shall come again the seventh day, and shall
look: and, behold, \add if\add* the plague be spread in the walls
of the house;

And if the plague come again, and break out in the house,
after that he hath taken away the stones, and after he hath scraped
the house, and after it is plaistered;

And if he that hath the issue spit upon him that is clean;
then he shall wash his clothes, and bathe \add himself\add* in water,
and be unclean until the even.

Thus shall ye separate the children of Israel from their uncleanness;
that they die not in their uncleanness, when they defile my tabernacle that
\add is\add* among them.

Do not prostitute thy daughter, to cause her to be a whore;
lest the land fall to whoredom, and the land become full of wickedness.\f + \fr 19.29 
\ft prostitute: Heb. profane\f*

And I will set my face against that man, and will cut him off
from among his people; because he hath given of his seed unto Molech,
to defile my sanctuary, and to profane my holy name.

And the man that lieth with his father’s wife hath uncovered
his father’s nakedness: both of them shall surely be put to death;
their blood \add shall be\add* upon them.

And if a woman approach unto any beast, and lie down thereto, thou shalt
kill the woman, and the beast: they shall surely be put to death;
their blood \add shall be\add* upon them.

And the \nd LORD\nd* said unto Moses, Speak unto the priests
the sons of Aaron, and say unto them, There shall none be defiled
for the dead among his people:

They shall not take a wife \add that is\add* a whore, or profane;
neither shall they take a woman put away from her husband: for he
\add is\add* holy unto his God.

I \add am\add* the \nd LORD\nd* your God, which brought you
forth out of the land of Egypt, that ye should not be their bondmen;
and I have broken the bands of your yoke, and made you go upright.

If they shall confess their iniquity, and the iniquity of their
fathers, with their trespass which they trespassed against me, and that also they have
walked contrary unto me;

And if \add a man\add* sanctify unto the \nd LORD\nd* a field
which he hath bought, which \add is\add* not of the fields of his
possession;
